'''Tsukahara Kofun''' (塚原古墳)
* {{ill|Tsukahara Kofun Group (Tama)|ja|塚原古墳群 (多摩市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukahara Kofun Group (Tama)|qq=}} - Located in [[:en:Tama, Tokyo|Tama, Tokyo]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo Prefecture]] in the Wada area. A kofun group from the late [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]]. * {{ill|Tsukahara Kofun Group (Iida)|ja|塚原古墳群 (飯田市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukahara Kofun Group (Iida)|qq=}} - Located in [[:en:Iida, Nagano|Iida, Nagano]], [[:en:Nagano Prefecture|Nagano Prefecture]]. Includes the Tsukahara Futagotsuka Kofun, a 67-meter-long keyhole-shaped kofun designated as a city historic site. * {{ill|Tsukahara Kofun (Shima)|ja|塚原古墳 (志摩市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukahara Kofun (Shima)|qq=}} - A circular kofun that once existed in [[:en:Shima, Mie|Shima, Mie]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], now lost. * {{ill|Tsukahara Kofun Group (Takatsuki)|ja|塚原古墳群 (高槻市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukahara Kofun Group (Takatsuki)|qq=}} - Located in [[:en:Takatsuki|Takatsuki]], [[:en:Osaka Prefecture|Osaka Prefecture]]. Once included 15 groups with about 110 kofun, collectively called Tsukahara Yajōzuka. Discovered by [[:en:William Gowland|William Gowland]] in 1872, these kofun were pivotal in early research of ancient Kofuns. * [[:en:Tsukawara Kofun Cluster|Tsukahara Kofun Group (Kumamoto)]] - Located in {{ill|Minami-ku, Kumamoto|ja|熊本市南区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minami-ku, Kumamoto|qq=}}, [[:en:Kumamoto Prefecture|Kumamoto Prefecture]]. A designated National Historic Site, developed as Tsukahara Kofun Park with 77 Kofuns including keyhole-shaped, square-ditch, and circular kofun. Surveys suggest around 500 kofun may exist in the area, with 203 confirmed. * {{ill|Iwahara Kofun Group|ja|岩原古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwahara Kofun Group|qq=}} (Tsukahara Kofun in Yamaga) - Part of the Iwahara Kofun Group in [[:en:Yamaga, Kumamoto|Yamaga, Kumamoto]], Kumamoto. Consists of nine circular Kofuns designated as a National Historic Site. Nearby are the Iwahara Horizontal Burial Chambers, a prefectural historic site.
